# --- Two terminals: (1) frontend: npm run dev -> :3000 (2) gemini-image-to-react-backend: npm run dev -> :8080 ---
# BACKEND_URL port MUST match the backend terminal log "Server running on port ____".
# --- Server-only (Next.js API routes) — required for /api/generate and /api/image-to-react proxies ---
# Prefer IPv4 loopback (Express binds 127.0.0.1):
BACKEND_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8080

# Client-visible base for image-to-react when needed:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/image-to-react
#
# Env cache: Next.js reads .env* at dev server start. After editing .env.local, restart `npm run dev`.
# If values still look stale, delete frontend/.next and restart (clean build: `next build` also refreshes).

# Do not put GEMINI_API_KEY in the frontend — set it only in gemini-image-to-react-backend/.env
